From f11eadc1e3ea172afa34c9a9a91feb371c75aa18 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arpitha Ramesha <arpirame@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 14 Aug 2025 21:12:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k: Remove stats_disable check from TLV parsing

Always parse the stats for HTT_PPDU_STATS_TAG_USR_COMMON,ensured
this by removing stats_disable check from TLV parsing function.
This function is responsible for parsing important TLV 
fields and assigning the struct for post-processing.The check was
incorrectly preventing proper parsing of critical TLVs

This is an existing change in 13.0 (added by
982-02-UPSTREAM-CP-DP-wifi-ath12k-Add-telemetry-stats-for-QCA-.patch)
Porting the same

Fixes: 98811828c60d ("add telemetry and vendor support for ErP and energy services")

Patch-dependency:
0130-15-UPSTREAM-CP-wifi-ath12k-Use-HTT_PPDU_STATS-for-tx-completion-sta.patch

Signed-off-by: Arpitha Ramesha <arpirame@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp_htt.c
@@ -239,11 +239,6 @@ static int ath12k_htt_tlv_ppdu_stats_par
 				    len, tag);
 			return -EINVAL;
 		}
-		/* No need to use these stats when SW is already
-		 * doing it on a per packet basis
-		 */
-		if (!ab->stats_disable)
-			break;
 		peer_id = ((struct htt_ppdu_stats_user_common *)ptr)->sw_peer_id;
 		cur_user = ath12k_get_ppdu_user_index(&ppdu_info->ppdu_stats,
 						      peer_id);
